<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="author" content="">
    <link rel="icon" href="img/Icon.ico">

    <title>Slurp</title>

    <!-- Bootstrap core CSS -->
    <link href="css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Custom styles for this template -->
    <link href="css/jumbotron-narrow.css" rel="stylesheet">

  </head>

  <body>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="header clearfix">
        <img class="pull-left" alt="Slurp" height="70" width="166" src="img/Logo.png"/>
        <nav>
          <ul class="nav nav-pills pull-right" style="padding-top: 20px">
            <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#">Home</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>

      </div>

      <div class="jumbotron">
        <h1>Slack to Dropbox</h1>
        <p class="lead">Conveniently sync files posted in Slack channels to any Dropbox account. No need to manually download files ever again.</p>

        <a href="https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?scope=bot,files:read,im:write,chat:write:bot,im:history&client_id=<%=ENV['SLACK_CLIENT_ID']%>">
        <img alt="Add to Slack" height="40" width="139" src="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png" srcset="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack.png 1x, https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/add_to_slack@2x.png 2x"/></a>
      </div>

      <div class="row marketing">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <h4>Simple</h4>
          <p>Set up the integration in minutes simply by logging into Slack and Dropbox.</p>

          <h4>Instantaneous</h4>
          <p>Files will be sent to Dropbox the moment they get posted in Slack.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <h4>Customizable</h4>
          <p>Invite the Slurp bot to only those channels you want to sync.</p>

          <h4>Never too late</h4>
          <p>Already have a ton of old files in Slack? Simply ask the Slurp bot to grab those, too.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <footer class="footer">
        <p>&copy; 2016 Slurp</p>
        <p style="color:#FF0000">DISCLAIMER: Slurp is a hobby project and has not been audited for security. Slurp is not suited for applications involving the exchange of confidential / sensitive information. Use at your own risk. The author assumes no responsibility for any breaches that result from the use of Slurp.</p>
      </footer>

    </div> <!-- /container -->

  </body>
</html>
